# Enterprise UX Constitution — Action Center & Context Workspace

Frozen interaction model for Catalyst One (and reusable across ecosystem platforms).

1. Users never leave their current business context for routine actions.
2. Action Center launches Context Workspaces (slide-over temporary workspaces, not CRM popups).
3. Context Workspaces are dynamically composed from Enterprise Registries (recipients, templates, documents, permissions).
4. Communication is relationship-aware and context-aware — no manual recipient address entry during transaction processing.
5. Templates are intelligent and filtered by recipient type, product, workflow stage, and transaction context.
6. Business communications enter the Enterprise Outbox (review timer) before dispatch; Send Now is an intentional override.
7. Chanakya is available inside every Context Workspace.
8. Timeline, Audit Trail, and Communication History update automatically after dispatch.
9. This model is reusable across Customer, Opportunity, Loan File, Wealth Partner, Lender, and future modules.

Prefer alignment with `src/components/catalyst-one/action-center/` rather than inventing parallel action menus or navigation-based compose flows.

Header rule: one Enterprise Workspace Header per screen; never duplicate identity chips/CTAs. Navigation actions (Open Credit Workbench, Open Loan Workspace, Add/Edit Contact) belong in Action Center — not as permanent header buttons.
